      "span_text": "In fact, monitoring autophagy flux is the most relevant way for the estimation of autophagic activity.   The commonly used assay for monitoring autophagy flux is the turnover of LC3B or SQSTM1/p62 using immunoblotting, which measures the content through autophagy flux; however, this approach is time-consuming and the results are often varied in different experimental settings and hard to interpret."
